{"title_page": "Badshah (rapper)", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian Rapper}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2016}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Badshah\n| background       = solo_singer\n| image            = Badshah spotted before the shoot of No Filter Neha.jpg\n| caption          = \n| birth_name       = Aditya Prateek Singh Sisodia\n| alias            = Badshah<br>Bad Boy Shah<br>Gabru Ghatak\n| birth_date       = <!--Birthdate must be attributed to a reliable published source with an established reputation for fact-checking. No blogs. No IMDb. No public records. See WP:BLPPRIVACY-->\n| birth_place      = <!--Must be attributed to a reliable published source with an established reputation for fact-checking. No blogs, no IMDb.-->\n| genre            = {{flat list|\n* [[Bhangra (music)|Bhangra]]\n* [[Desi hip hop]]\n* [[Reggaeton]]\n* [[Bollywood music|Bollywood]]\n* [[R&B]] \n* [[Pop music|Pop]]\n}}\n| occupation       = {{ubl|Singer|rapper}}\n| years_active     = 2006\u2013present\n| associated_acts  = {{flat list|\n* [[Aastha Gill]]\n* [[Yo Yo Honey Singh]]\n* [[Tilak Raj]]\n* [[Navv Inder]]\n* [[Now United]]\n}}\n| website          =\n| label            = {{flat list|\n* [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]\n* [[Zee Music Company]]\n* [[Sony Music India]]\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Aditya Prateek Singh Sisodia''', better known by his stage name '''Badshah''',<ref>Godha, Ronak (19 February 2016) [https://web.archive.org/web/20160222013242/http://edyoucatives.com/watch-badshah-live-musical-concert-ft-aastha-gill-dj-rebirth-on-21st-feb Badshah Live Musical Concert \u2013 Ft. Aastha Gill & DJ Rebirth on 21st Feb]. EdYouCatives</ref><ref>[http://www.hindustantimes.com/chandigarh/packed-in-promise/article1-1169384.aspx Packed in promise | chandigarh]. Hindustan Times (5 January 2014). Retrieved on 2015-10-16.</ref><ref>[http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/music/i-dont-want-to-compose-bollywood-albums-badshah/ I don't want to compose Bollywood albums: Badshah]. The Indian Express (14 June 2015). Retrieved on 10 August 2015.</ref> is an Indian [[rapper]] and singer known for his [[Hindi]], [[Haryanvi]], and [[Punjabi language|Punjabi]] songs.<ref name=TOI>{{cite web|last1=Gupta|first1=Priya|title=Badshah uses Honey Singh's fame by giving negative statements against him |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/music/news/Badshah-doesnt-want-to-use-Honey-Singhs-fame/articleshow/38992422.cms|publisher=Times of India|accessdate=10 February 2015}}</ref> He started his career in 2006 alongside [[Yo Yo Honey Singh]] in his hip hop group Mafia Mundeer. He split from Honey in 2012 and released his independent Haryanvi song ''Kar Gayi Chull'', which was later adopted into the 2016 [[Bollywood]] movie, ''[[Kapoor & Sons]]''. His music has been featured in [[Bollywood]] soundtracks for films such as 2014 films ''[[Humpty Sharma Ki Dulhania]]''<ref>{{cite web|last1=Maheshwri|first1=Neha|title=Saturday Saturday maker Badshah: I'm an artiste, not a preacher|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/music/news/Saturday-Saturday-maker-Badshah-Im-an-artiste-not-a-preacher/articleshow/37711133.cms|publisher=Times of India|accessdate=10 February 2015}}</ref> and ''[[Khoobsurat (2014 film)|Khoobsurat]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Bhasin|first1=Shivani|title=Music Review: Badshah replaces Honey Singh but Khoobsurat's soundtrack is a mess|url=http://www.firstpost.com/bollywood/music-review-badshah-replaces-honey-singh-but-khoobsurats-soundtrack-is-a-mess-1706181.html|publisher=First Post|accessdate=10 February 2015}}</ref>\n\nHis debut single, \"[[DJ Waley Babu]]\" featuring [[Aastha Gill]], was ranked number one on the Indian iTunes charts within 24 hours of the release. The song crossed a million views on YouTube within 30 hours.<ref>[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/music/news/Badshah-DJ-waley-babu-not-regular-party-song/articleshow/48251177.cms Badshah: 'DJ waley babu' not regular party song]. Times of India (28 July 2015)</ref>  In 2016, he collaborated with [[Navv Inder]] on \"Wakhra Swag\" which won the 2016 Punjabi Music Awards for best duo/group and most popular song of the year award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yespunjab.com/punjabi-music/item/92845-winners-of-ptc-punjabi-music-awards-2016-held-at-jalandhar-complete-list|title=Winners of PTC Punjabi Music Awards 2016 held at Jalandhar|author=Jalandhar|publisher=Yes Punjab News|date=26 May 2016|accessdate=15 August 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160529025939/http://www.yespunjab.com/punjabi-music/item/92845-winners-of-ptc-punjabi-music-awards-2016-held-at-jalandhar-complete-list|archive-date=29 May 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://punjabikhurki.com/ptc-music-awards-2016/|title=PTC Music Awards 2016\u2013 Here Is The Complete List Of Winners!|author=Amneet Kaur|publisher=Punjabi Khurki|date=27 May 2016|accessdate=15 August 2016}}</ref>\n\nHe has appeared in ''[[Forbes India]]''{{'s}} [[Forbes Celebrity 100|Celebrity 100]] in 2017, 2018 and 2019 as one of the highest-paid celebrities in India.<ref>{{cite web |title=Badshah - 2019 Celebrity 100 |url=https://www.forbesindia.com/celebprofile2019/badshah/1819/115 |website=[[Forbes India]] |accessdate=31 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and family==\nBadshah was born in [[Delhi]], to a father from [[Haryana]] and a mother from [[Punjab, India|Punjab]].<ref name=\"IANS\">{{cite news |title=Badshah buys Rolls Royce Wraith priced at Rs 6.4 crore, says \u2018Apna time aa gaya\u2019 |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/badshah-buys-rolls-royce-wraith-priced-at-rs-6-4-crore-says-apna-time-aa-gaya/story-xEm0gWI1ZLzL5D1oh4c2tI.html |accessdate=23 February 2020 |work=HIndustan Times |agency=[[Indo-Asian News Service]] (IANS) |date=30 April 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190501094345/https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/badshah-buys-rolls-royce-wraith-priced-at-rs-6-4-crore-says-apna-time-aa-gaya/story-xEm0gWI1ZLzL5D1oh4c2tI.html |archivedate=1 May 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"bdshah\">[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/music/news/Whenever-I-need-inspiration-I-go-to-Delhi-Badshah/articleshow/38137665.cms Whenever I need inspiration, I go to Delhi: Badshah], ''[[The Times of India]]'' (11 July 2014). Retrieved on 2015-10-16.</ref> He is married to Jasmine.<ref name=bad1>[http://daily.bhaskar.com/news/ENT-BOW-did-you-know-bad-boy-badshaah-is-a-cute-loving-husband-in-real-meet-his-adorable-5169454-PHO.html Did you know bad boy Badshah is a cute loving husband in real! Meet his adorable wife], [[Dainik Bhaskar]], 16 Nov 2015.</ref>\n\nHe completed his schooling from [[Bal Bharati Public School|Bal Bharti Public School]], Pitampura, Delhi where he performed with his school choir.<ref name=\"bdshah\"/> Prior to becoming a full-time musician he enrolled as a math student at the prestigious [[Banaras Hindu University]] in Varanasi before moving to civil engineer at [[Punjab Engineering College|PEC]], [[Chandigarh]], where he was exposed to new [[Punjabi language|Punjabi]] music which promoted him to take on \"rap\" writing. He has stated that if he had not become a rapper, he may have become an IAS officer.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Hebbar|first1=Prajakta|title='If I wasn't a rapper, I'd have been an IAS officer': Everything you wanted to know about Badshah, who calls himself a 'prime-time' version of Honey Singh|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/if-i-wasnt-a-rapper-id-have-been-an-ias-officer-everything-you-wanted-to-know-about-badshah-who-calls-himself-a-primetime-version-of-honey-singh/495965-8-66.html|publisher=IBN Live|accessdate=10 February 2015}}</ref><ref>[http://kerala.indiaeveryday.in/fullnews-i-dont-want-to-compose-bollywood-albums-badshah-1190-627952.htm I don't want to compose Bollywood albums: Badshah \u2013 Full News] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150619132529/http://kerala.indiaeveryday.in/fullnews-i-dont-want-to-compose-bollywood-albums-badshah-1190-627952.htm |date=19 June 2015 }}. Kerala.indiaeveryday.in. Retrieved on 10 August 2015.</ref><ref>[http://m.hindustantimes.com/chandigarh/packed-in-promise/article1-1169384.aspx Packed in promise]. hindustantimes.com (5 January 2014). Retrieved on 10 August 2015.</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/badshah-i-still-have-my-st-stephens-id-that-is-something-worth-flaunting/articleshow/64973935.cms|title=Badshah: I still have my St Stephen's ID, that is something worth flaunting|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2019-06-09}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nHe started his career in the music industry with the name \"Cool Equal\", but then changed his name to Badshah.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ghaintpunjab.com/GhaintPunjab/Article/13965/aditya-prateek-singh-sisodia-cool-equal-old%20name-badshah|title=Aditya Prateek Singh Sisodia Was 'Cool Equal' Before Finally Becoming 'Badshah'!|website=Ghaint Punjab|access-date=2019-06-09}}</ref>\n\nHis 2019 song \"Paagal\" reached 74.8 million views on [[YouTube]] within 24 hours, setting the record for the [[List of most-viewed online videos in the first 24 hours|most-viewed video in 24 hours]] on YouTube.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/videos/entertainment/hindi/rapper-badshah-becomes-first-indian-artist-to-create-world-record-with-his-latest-track-paagal/videoshow/70189336.cms|title=Rapper Badshah becomes first Indian artist to create world record with his latest track 'Paagal' {{!}} Hindi Movie News - Bollywood - Times of India|website=timesofindia.indiatimes.com|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref> [[BTS (band)|BTS]] fans claimed that the artist had bought the views to cross the global record due to his low number of likes in the first 24 hours, but YouTube did not confirm whether the views are real or fake. The song also did not appear in the 100-position Global Top Music Videos chart for the week. However, Badshah denied it was fake views, but admitted his record label [[Sony Music India]] bought paid ads.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/8520387/indian-rapper-badshah-video-one-day-youtube-record-sony|title=Six Days After Sony Says Indian Rapper's Video Broke One-Day Record for Views, YouTube Has Yet to Confirm|website=Billboard.com|access-date=2019-07-28}}</ref>\n\nAn explanation for YouTube not acknowledging the record was that Badshah's record label Sony Music India had purchased advertisements from [[Google]] and YouTube that embedded the video or directed fans to it in some way. However, it has emerged that this is a common practice in the global [[music industry]], and that similar practices had previously been used by the record labels of previous record holders such as Ariana Grande and Blackpink. This has cast doubt on some of the 24-hour viewership records on YouTube.<ref name=\"bloomberg\">{{cite news |title=Bollywood Rapper Sets Viewer Record YouTube Isn\u2019t Talking About |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-07-30/bollywood-rapper-sets-viewer-record-youtube-isn-t-talking-about |accessdate=20 September 2019 |agency=[[Bloomberg News]] |date=30 July 2019}}</ref>\n\nHis song \"Genda Phool\" was released by [[Sony Music India]] in 2020. It had mixing with a [[Bengali language|Bengali]] folk song \"Boro Loker Biti Lo\". Ratan Kahar, a Bengali artist, claimed to be the original writer and composer of the folk song.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://zeenews.india.com/bengali/entertainment/exclusive-interview-bengali-folk-artist-ratan-kahar-claim-he-is-the-writer-and-composer-of-boroloker-bitilo_307857.html|title='\u0986\u0987\u09a8\u09bf \u09b2\u09a1\u09bc\u09be\u0987\u09af\u09bc\u09c7 \u09af\u09be\u0993\u09af\u09bc\u09be\u09b0 \u0986\u09b0\u09cd\u09a5\u09bf\u0995 \u09b8\u09be\u09ae\u09b0\u09cd\u09a5\u09cd\u09af \u09a8\u09c7\u0987', '\u09ac\u09a1\u09bc\u09b2\u09cb\u0995\u09c7\u09b0 \u09ac\u09bf\u099f\u09bf \u09b2\u09cb' \u09a8\u09bf\u09af\u09bc\u09c7 \u0986\u0995\u09cd\u09b7\u09c7\u09aa\u09c7\u09b0 \u09b8\u09c1\u09b0 \u09b0\u09a4\u09a8 \u0995\u09be\u09b9\u09be\u09b0\u09c7\u09b0|date=2020-03-28|website=Zee24Ghanta.com|access-date=2020-03-31}} </ref> Though Badshah later released a statement saying that it was a traditional [[Baul]] [[Folk music|folk song]] which was not copyrighted, since folk music does not fall under copyright protections and is thus in the [[public domain]].<ref>{{Cite tweet|number=1245014731552772097|user=Its_Badshah|title=Please read|author=Badshah|date=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n\n=== Singles ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#cfc; text-align:center;\"\n|'''Year'''\n|'''Song'''\n|'''Label'''\n|'''Language'''\n|'''Note(s)'''\n|'''Reference(s)'''\n|-\n|2012\n|\"Saturday Saturday\" <small>(Indeep Bakshi featuring Badshah)</small>\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[Sony Music Entertainment]]\n|Hindi\n|\n|<ref>{{Citation|title=Saturday Saturday by Indeep Bakshi & Badshah|date=2012-08-17|url=https://www.saavn.com/s/album/hindi/Saturday-Saturday-2012/TxYr4ex-R2s_|accessdate=2017-06-28}}</ref>\n|-\n|2013\n|[[Proper Patola]] <small>([[Diljit Dosanjh]] featuring Badshah)</small>\n| rowspan=\"6\" |Punjabi\n|\n|<ref>{{Citation|title=Proper Patola by Diljit Dosanjh|date=2013-08-09|url=https://www.saavn.com/s/album/punjabi/Proper-Patola-2013/3bzZ1Jw9I80_|accessdate=2017-06-28}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2014\n|\"Chull\" <small>(Fazilpuria featuring Badshah)</small>\n|\n|<ref>{{Citation|title=Chull by Fazilpuria|date=2014-06-16|url=https://www.saavn.com/s/album/punjabi/Chull-2014/IbAXYrk5Fd8_|accessdate=2017-06-28}}</ref>\n|-\n|\"Bandook\" <small>(with Raxstar)</small>\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[MTV India]]\n|\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" |2015\n|\"Desi Hiphop\" <small>([[Manj Musik]] featuring Roach Killer, Raxstar, Humble the Poet, Big Dhillon, Badshah, Sarb Smooth, [[Raftaar (rapper)|Raftaar]])</small>\n|\